Privacy Policy

Last Updated: November 2025

1. Introduction

This policy explains how k0ff Gestion collects, processes, and protects user data on Discord.
Respecting user privacy and ensuring data security are top priorities for the Developer, ins.ciable.

2. Data Collected

The Bot does not collect any sensitive personal data (IP address, email, location, etc.).
The only data that may be processed are technical Discord-related information, such as:

User, server, or message IDs,

Discord username and tag (only if required for a command),

Message content in the context of command execution (never stored permanently).

This data is used only temporarily.

3. Purpose of Processing

Collected data is used exclusively to:

Execute the Bot’s features,

Identify permissions and manage moderation,

Prevent abuse and ensure service stability.

No data is used for marketing, commercial, or statistical purposes.

4. Retention and Deletion

Temporary data generated by the Bot (logs, errors, internal statistics) is:

Retained for a limited period,

Automatically deleted after use,

Never shared with unauthorized third parties.

Users may request deletion of their data at any time (if applicable) via the contact below.

5. Sharing and Disclosure

The Developer does not share any user data with third parties, except in the following cases:

If required by law or a judicial authority,

If requested by Discord to enforce its Terms of Service.

No data is sold or used for advertising purposes.

6. Security

All data is processed via secure servers and protected against unauthorized access.
Technical measures (authentication, encryption, access restrictions) are applied to ensure the Bot’s security.

7. User Rights

Users may:

Request information about any data that may have been collected,

Request the deletion or anonymization of such data.

All requests can be sent to:
Discord: ins.ciable

8. Policy Updates

This policy may be updated at any time to reflect changes to the Bot or applicable laws.
The date of the latest update is indicated at the top of this document.
Continued use of the Bot after changes constitutes implicit acceptance of the updates.

9. Contact

For any questions or complaints, contact:
Discord: ins.ciable
Support: https://discord.gg/RZShC9geeZ
